(96, 'https://elektro.um.ac.id/2020/01/27/kesempatan-mengikuti-robot-master-taiwan', 'Kesempatan Mengikuti Road to Master in Robotics, Taipei Tech – Taiwan - Departemen Teknik Elektro dan Informatika UM - FT - UM', 'Opportunities are opened for all students majoring in Electrical Engineering to take part in student exchange activities organized by the Assistive Robotic Lab which was fostered by Prof. Hsien-I Lin with contributions to the fields of robotics, electronics, image processing, and artificial intelligence. Opportunities are also opened for those who wish to continue their master’s study in this lab. The program will be held for 3 months in Taipei, Taiwan and gets an allowance every month. Internship will take place before September 2020. The required requirements are:\nThe document must be printed and submitted to the administrative staff (in 2nd floor of H5 building) the Electrical Engineering Department.\nCP : Mrs. Siti Sendari (+62 853-3000-3362)'),
