(98, 'https://elektro.um.ac.id/2020/03/06/saga-university-program-for-academic-exchange-2020-2021-space-e-opportunities', 'Saga University Program for Academic Exchange 2020-2021 (Space-E) Opportunities - Departemen Teknik Elektro dan Informatika UM - FT - UM', 'SPACE-E students are able to register in courses throughout the university after consulting and obtaining permission from their academic advisor. Students in the Faculty of Science and Engineering and the Faculty of Agriculture will be required to conduct “independent study” with 2 or 4 credits. Their supervisor will provide guidance at the beginning of the period and necessary advice and assistance throughout the program. See the description in the overview of SPACE-E for more information. Almost all of the newly offered courses in the academic year of 2019 are given only with titles.\nTo all electrical engineering students who wish to take part in SPACE-E Program, please print required documents and submit to administrative staff in 2nd floor of H5 builidng.\ncontact person: +62 812-4967-4591 (Dr. Eng. Anik Nur Handayani, S.T., M.T.)'),
(99, 'https://elektro.um.ac.id/2020/03/06/mevlana-exchange-programme-2020-2021-opportunities', 'Mevlana Exchange Programme 2020-2021 Opportunities - Departemen Teknik Elektro dan Informatika UM - FT - UM', 'Mevlana Exchange Programme is a mobility programme (inbound and outbound) funded by The Council of Higher Education of Turkey (YOK) for students and academic staffs or Higher Education Institutions (HEI) which have signed the Mevlana Protocol. More Information can download here\nThe document must be emailed to Faculty of Engineering Academic staff eka.susi@um.ac.id'),
(100, 'https://elektro.um.ac.id/2018/03/13/tawaran-beasiswa-pemerintah-australia-program-australia-awards-indonesia-tahun-akademik-20192020', 'Tawaran Beasiswa Pemerintah Australia Program Australia Awards Indonesia Tahun Akademik 2019/2020 - Departemen Teknik Elektro dan Informatika UM - FT - UM', 'Pemerintah Australia melalui Department of Foreign Affairs and Trade (DFAT) meluncurkan program Australia Awards Scholarships untuk mengikuti pendidikan program pasca-sarjana (Master dan Doktor) di Australia. Berbagai tawaran beasiswa yang diberikan sesuai dengan bidang-bidang yang menjadi prioritas pembangunan nasional pada universitas-universitas di Australia.\nBagi para calon peserta yang memenuhi persyaratan dan telah melengkapi dokumen-dokumen yang dibutuhkan akan diundang untuk mengikuti wawancara dan tes bahasa Inggris dengan waktu dan tempat yang akan diberitahukan kemudian.\nBagi yang berminat dan telah memenuhi syarat dapat mendaftar secara online melalui http://oasis.dfat.gov.au, selambat-lambatnya pada tanggal 30 April 2018.\n*Untuk informasi lebih jelas mengenai program Australia Awards Scholarships 2018 Intake, dapat diakses melalui laman resmi Australia Awards di www.australiaawardsindonesia.org .\n—\nBiro Kerja Sama dan Komunikasi Publik\nKementerian Riset, Teknologi, dan Pendidikan Tinggi\n2018\nlampiran:\nLONG TERM AWARDS BROCHURE\nSumber : https://ristekdikti.go.id/australia-awards-scholarships/'),
(101, 'https://elektro.um.ac.id/2020/02/22/saga-university-program-for-academic-exchange-space-book-2019', 'Saga University Program for Academic Exchange (SPACE) Book 2019 - Departemen Teknik Elektro dan Informatika UM - FT - UM', 'Kepada seluruh civitas akademika TE UM, berikut ini dokumentasi kegiatan Saga University Program for Academic Exchange (SPACE) tahun 2019 yang dijalani oleh mahasiswa TE UM Noor Octavian Anwar dan Pamela Paula Maldini. Download disini.'),
